Between 1992 and 2017, the game of ballots and bullets claimed thousands of innocent lives, forcibly displaced hundreds of thousands and destroyed property worth billions.The 2010 Constitution ushered in an American-style pure presidential system. A decade after the 2010 Constitution came into force, Kenya’s transition is trapped. The country is yet to become an inclusive ‘developmental democracy’. In spite of that, its power elite is split over political reforms. But the train has left the station and the country is headed for a seismic referendum.



